{
  "texts": [
    "However, due to the dependence of fMRI on hemodynamic fluctuations associated with neural activity, it is unsuitable for capturing rapid transitions in brain functional connectivity configurations with high temporal resolution (Jamadar et al., 2021).",
    "Moreover, the spatial resolution of this technique is limited to a millimeter scale.",
    "As a result, our comprehension of the cellular mechanisms underlying the aberrant brain functional connectivity observed in schizophrenia remains incomplete.",
    "Multiple etiological hypotheses have been proposed to elucidate the abnormal brain connectivity seen in schizophrenia.",
    "The dopaminergic hypothesis posits that abnormal dopaminergic neurotransmission contributes to the development and manifestation of schizophrenia (Creese et al., 1976; Toda and Abi-Dargham, 2007)."
  ]
}